|CKBThree Roads, No Refunds|000

Syntax: croads train <misdirection|volatility|contraband>

Every Charlatan Rank after the first earns one road point. Spending it is
immediate and permanent, which is why the clerk asks you to spell the road.
Road awards stop after 30 points, enough to raise all three roads to ten.
Ranks after 30 build reputation and open advanced schemes instead.

  Misdirection
    Confuse the mark, manufacture openings, and throw your voice. Improves
    confuse and suckerpunch, and opens distract.

  Volatility
    Make corpse ash useful and meals suspicious. Opens cookash and concoct.
    Alchemy or Herbalism may still be required for a particular recipe.

  Contraband
    Load weapons and stretch acquired poisons. Alchemy and Smithing decide
    which dangerous ideas you can put into practice.

Use 'gscore charlatan' to see your Rank, guild XP, roads, spare points, and
relevant trade skills. Use 'chskills available' when you want the short answer
to, "What can I get away with today?"
